The paper discusses population protocols, which are a model of distributed computation, and their variations. This falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the effects of non-atomic interaction and unreliable communication, which are related to Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The study of expressive power is also related to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
